  "prompt": "Can you check your WhatsApp from another phone?",
  "response": "Yes, you can check your WhatsApp on another phone by using WhatsApp Web or by logging in to your account on the new phone. Here\u2019s how:\n\n1. **Using WhatsApp Web**:\n   - Open a web browser on the other phone.\n   - Go to the WhatsApp Web website (web.whatsapp.com).\n   - On your primary phone, open WhatsApp, tap on the three dots (menu) in the top right corner (for Android) or the Settings tab (for iPhone), and select \"Linked Devices.\"\n   - Tap on \"Link a Device\" and scan the QR code displayed on the browser using your primary phone.\n\n2. **Using Another Phone**:\n   - Install WhatsApp on the new phone.\n   - Open the app and go through the setup process.\n   - When prompted, enter the same phone number associated with your current WhatsApp account.\n   - You will receive a verification code via SMS. Enter that code to access your messages.\n\nKeep in mind that logging into WhatsApp on another phone will log you out of the previous device. Make sure you have access to the phone number used for verification.",
